data.name: King Industries
data.description:
We add the “performance” to a vast variety of products that are part of our daily lives, from the car you drive to the chips in your computer. Chances are, not a day goes by that you do not use a product that contains or has been manufactured using a King additive.

While our additive functions are technical by nature, in short these specialty chemicals impart desirable, value-added properties to the end uses they are apart of. Whether a King catalyst used to cure an automotive coating while saving energy or a King rust preventive extending a lubricant’s life, they indeed add the performance that a consumer expects from their product choices.

Often used at levels as low as parts per million, King additives, are an integral component to formulations of some of the biggest names in the chemical, rubber and oil industries worldwide. While many have been loyal customers for decades, we are constantly challenged by them and others to develop new products that provide even higher standards of performance. It is this challenge of providing innovative high performance additives that drives our business

data.name: NACURE
data.description: NACURE® acid catalysts accelerate the amino crosslinked reaction by reducing the temperature and time needed to cure the system. These systems are commonly used for primer and top coat formulations in the auto OEM market. Selecting the proper NACURE acid catalyst could improve the crosslinking of the final film. These tough high performance films can exhibit improved moisture/corrosion resistance, higher gloss, excellent exterior durability and improved adhesion.

data.name: K-CORR
data.description: K-CORR® and K-CORR® G rust inhibitor systems are specially designed to provide outstanding rust protection to greases exposed to severe salt water conditions.

data.name: NA-SUL
data.description: NA-SUL® rust and corrosion inhibitors exhibit superior salt fog performance compared to other sulfonate chemistries. Dinonylnaphthalene sulfonates are effective in a wide range of applications from general and indoor storage to harsh exterior applications. NA-SUL® corrosion inhibitors are effective on steel, galvanized steel, aluminum and various other metals. The NA-SUL® line provides excellent rust and corrosion protection in addition to other unique performance properties. King’s process of direct neutralization produces sulfonates with no chlorine, resulting in enhanced rust protection and resistance to staining.

data.name: DISPARLON
data.description: Addition of DISPARLON® provides thixotropy with good shear thinning for ease of application, gunability and excellent slump control/bead formation. DISPARLON provides a balanced mix of performance benefits for both waterborne and solventborne adhesive and sealant applications.

data.name: K-KAT
data.description: K-KAT® catalysts are alternatives (or substitutes) to tin and mercury catalysts for isocyanate, blocked isocyanate and moisture cure silane systems. K-KAT catalysts are effective for crosslinking silane terminated polymers while adding improved adhesion.

data.name: K-FLEX
data.description: K-FLEX® diols are solventless liquid polyester diols that range in viscosity from 400-12,000 cPs and can add a balance of flexibility while retaining hardness. They are especially suited for adhesives that require good clarity and low color development.

data.name: NA-SUL® CA-1259
data.description: NA-SUL® CA-1259 is a high performance liquid rust and corrosion inhibitor for rust preventives and dewatering fluids. It offers excellent solubility in a wide range of mineral oils, esters and vegetable oils. NA-SUL® CA-1259 is less viscous than many other additives of its type and may often be able to be cold blended into oils. This results in lower energy cost and faster processing. NA-SUL® CA-1259 has an exceptional ability to help to separate water from oil and oil/solvent solutions making it very suitable for dewatering fluid applications. The solubility of NA-SUL® CA-1259 should be verified in the diluents that are being considered for use.

data.name: NA-SUL® CA-50
data.description: NA-SUL® CA-50 is a premium non-staining rust and corrosion inhibitor with excess alkalinity in the form of oil-soluble calcium carbonate.

data.name: NA-LUBE® AW-6400FG
data.description: NA-LUBE® AW-6400FG is an ashless rust and corrosion inhibitor and antiwear additive.

data.name: NA-SUL® CA-770FG
data.description: NA-SUL® CA-770FG is a premium rust inhibitor for petroleum and synthetic lubricants, greases, and rust preventive fluids. It provides excellent demulsibility and filterability and is compatible with a wide range of additives and base stocks.

data.name: NA-LUBE® AO-142
data.description: NA-LUBE® AO-142 is a liquid diphenylamine based antioxidant for synthetic and mineral oil based lubricants and greases.

data.name: NA-SUL® BSN
data.description: NA-SUL® BSN is a premium non-staining rust inhibitor for petroleum and synthetic lubricants, greases, rust preventive fluids and metalworking specialties. It provides excellent demulsibility and resistance to the negative effects of water and is compatible with a wide range of additives and base oils.

data.name: NA-LUBE® AW-6310
data.description: NA-LUBE® AW-6310 is an ashless multifunctional additive for industrial and automotive lubricants and greases. NA-LUBE® AW-6310, when used at very low treat levels, exhibits excellent extreme pressure and antiwear properties as determined with the FZG test rig. Additionally, NA-LUBE® AW-6310 imparts outstanding steel corrosion protection and demulsibility to lubricants based on Group I, II and synthetic base stocks.

data.name: NA-SUL® 729
data.description: NA-SUL® 729 is a premium rust inhibitor for petroleum and synthetic lubricants, greases, rust preventive fluids and metalworking specialties. It provides excellent demulsibility and filterability, both dry and wet, and is compatible with a wide range of additives and base stocks. It is also a good dispersant for solids used in lubricants.

data.name: NA-SUL® ZS
data.description: NA-SUL® ZS is a premium rust inhibitor for petroleum and synthetic lubricants and greases. It offers excellent demulsibility, improved oxidative stability, and resistance to the effects of water.

DISPARLON provides a balanced mix of performance benefits for both waterborne and solventborne adhesive and sealant applications.
data.seo_description: Addition of DISPARLON® provides thixotropy with good shear thinning for ease of application, gunability and excellent slump control/bead formation. DISPARLON provides a balanced mix of performance ben

data.name: DISPARLON® 6200
data.description: DISPARLON® 6200 is a powdered thixotropic agent based on amide wax. The low activation temperature required to build a strong thixotropic network prevents slumping of sealants and adhesives. It is especially effective in MS polymer and epoxy systems.

data.name: DISPARLON® 6250
data.description: DISPARLON® 6250 is a cost effective powdered thixotropic agent based on amide wax. Low activation temperature required to build a strong thixotropic network which prevents slumping of sealants and adhesives. Especially suited for MS sealant and silicone systems.

data.name: DISPARLON® 6300
data.description: DISPARLON® 6300 is a hybrid powdered thixotropic agent based on amide wax. Low activation temperature is required to build a strong thixotropic network which provides excellent anti-sag properties along with good recoatability and minimal viscosity increase. It is especially effective in epoxy coatings and adhesives.

data.name: DISPARLON® 6500
data.description: DISPARLON® 6500 is a unique non-reactive polyamide thixotrope supplied as a powder. Through heat activation a strong thixotropic network provides strong anti-sagging and Anti-slumping without seeding or loss of effectiveness on aging. It is effective in caotings, sealants and adhesives formulations.

data.name: DISPARLON® 6650
data.description: DISPARLON® 6650 is a powder polyamide which, through heat activation, develops a strong thixotropic network, providing excellent anti-sag properties and improved recoatability to coatings while being cost effective.

data.name: DISPARLON® 6700
data.description: DISPARLON® 6700 is a powder polyamide which, through heat activation, develops a strong thixotropic network, providing excellent anti-sag properties particularly for high build epoxies.

data.name: DISPARLON® A603-20X
data.description: DISPARLON® A603-20X is an alcohol-free pre-activated polyamide developed for isocyanate cured paint systems. it can be used on both the polyol and isocyante side of the formulation for anti-settling and anti-sag control.

data.name: DISPARLON® A650-20X
data.description: DISPARLON® A650-20X is a pre-activated polyamide thixotropic agent. When dispersed it is highly efficient in high build epoxy systems for anti-settling and anti-sag properties.

data.name: DISPARLON® A671-EZ
data.description: DISPARLON® A671-EZ is an easy to use, post addable pre-activated polyamide thixotropic agent in mineral spirits. Recommended for DIY and industrial stains for anti-settling and pigment orientation. It is a softer paste version of A670-20M.

data.name: DISPARLON® 6900-20X
data.description: DISPARLON® 6900-20X is a thixotropic agent in paste form consisting of a dispersion of swollen particles of a unique synthetic amide wax. It is easily incorporated into many vehicles and/or solvents and develops an exceptionally strong and long retained thixotropic structure.

data.name: DISPARLON® EZ-777
data.description: DISPARLON® EZ-777 is an easily dispersible paste of specially activated synthetic amide wax. It is easily incorporated into many solventborne systems to develop an exceptionally strong and long retained thixotropic structure.

data.name: DISPARLON® 6100
data.description: DISPARLON® 6100 is a powdered thixotropic agent based on amide wax. Lowest activation temperature required to build a strong thixotropic network which prevents slumping of sealants and adhesives. Especially suited for MMA/MS polymer sealants.
